snippet.textDisplay: Sooooo, natural development of the immune system is out the window? I mean, there isn’t a vaccine for everything, and if we start being germophobes, how do any of us know the long term effects on the development of our species? Washing your hands is a given, but completely replacing physical contact? What happens when everybody has no active and adapted immune systems, and a truly terrifying virus sweeps through the globe and is killing everybody? I feel it’s a case of us allowing natural fluctuations in our population in relations to deaths from disease, or one day a disease will wipe most of us out for real. I mean, a lot of the deadly cases here in the US are people with high blood pressure who weren’t taking their medication, leading to hypertension. Germs are the least of our problems when we can’t even make ourselves take the medication we need to live during a pandemic.

snippet.textDisplay:
Hey Mark!

I LOVE your stuff. But very few people think it is okay to go to work when ill. Most folks who work ill are forced to do so by their employer. Many times even an illness with a doctor's note is still given 'points' and after so many points per period of time, you are written up or even fired. Not to mention how many places simply do not have any or enough paid sick leave. Which leaves many in the position of having to chose between going to work ill and basic necessities. Furthermore one regularly hears of attempts to call being met with some ultimatums or even an insistence to come in anyways.

I simply implore you to urge the change of social norm here towards the companies who do not care about the health of their employees and insist either directly or indirectly for them to come in while ill.

Lots of Love! <3
